        <div class="container">
            <div class="policy-header">
                <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
                <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: May 31, 2026</p>
            </div>

            <div class="policy-content">
                <section class="policy-section">
                    <h2>1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
                    <p>By accessing and using TauchoPortal ("Service"), you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree with any part of these terms, you may not use our Service. TauchoPortal ("Company," "we," "us," "our") reserves the right to modify these terms at any time, and your continued use of the Service constitutes acceptance of any changes.</p>
                </section>

                <section class="policy-section">
                    <h2>2. Description of Service</h2>
                    <p>TauchoPortal is a cloud-based streaming automation platform that monitors your live streaming channels across multiple platforms (YouTube, Twitch, NicoNico) and automatically triggers actions on connected smart devices based on stream events such as comments, donations, reactions, and audience engagement.</p>
                </section>

                <section class="policy-section">
                    <h2>3. User Eligibility and Account Registration</h2>
                    
                    <h3>3.1 Age Requirement</h3>
                    <p>You must be at least 13 years of age to use TauchoPortal. By registering, you represent and warrant that you are at least 13 years old and have the legal authority to enter into this agreement.</p>

                    <h3>3.2 Account Information</h3>
                    <p>You are responsible for:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Providing accurate, current, and complete account information</li>
                        <li>Maintaining the confidentiality of your password and account credentials</li>
                        <li>Notifying us immediately of unauthorized access or use</li>
                        <li>All activities that occur under your account</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>3.3 Account Termination</h3>
                    <p>We reserve the right to terminate or suspend your account at any time, for any reason, without notice, including for violation of these Terms of Service.</p>
                </section>

                <section class="policy-section">
                    <h2>4. Streaming Platform Integration</h2>
                    
                    <h3>4.1 Third-Party Permissions</h3>
                    <p>To use TauchoPortal, you must authorize the Service to access your streaming platform accounts through OAuth authentication. You grant us permission to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Access your channel information and stream status</li>
                        <li>Monitor chat messages and viewer interactions</li>
                        <li>Retrieve stream metrics and analytics</li>
                        <li>Detect live stream events and interactions</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>4.2 Compliance with Platform Terms</h3>
                    <p>You are solely responsible for complying with the Terms of Service of all streaming platforms you use (YouTube, Twitch, NicoNico, etc.). We are not liable for any violations of third-party platform terms or policies.</p>

                    <h3>4.3 Revocation of Access</h3>
                    <p>You may revoke TauchoPortal's access to your streaming accounts at any time through your platform's settings. Upon revocation, we will cease monitoring and cease access to your channel data.</p>
                </section>

                <section class="policy-section">
                    <h2>5. Smart Device Integration</h2>
                    
                    <h3>5.1 Device Ownership</h3>
                    <p>You represent and warrant that you own or have authorization to control all smart devices you register with TauchoPortal. You are solely responsible for ensuring that the use of these devices complies with all applicable laws and regulations.</p>

                    <h3>5.2 Device Control Authorization</h3>
                    <p>By registering a smart device, you authorize TauchoPortal to send commands to that device based on the conditions and triggers you configure. You acknowledge that we are not responsible for device malfunctions or unintended actions.</p>

                    <h3>5.3 Safety Responsibility</h3>
                    <p>You are solely responsible for ensuring that automated device triggers do not create safety hazards. This includes ensuring that:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Devices do not interfere with essential services or safety systems</li>
                        <li>Automated actions do not endanger you or others</li>
                        <li>Device configurations are appropriate for your environment</li>
                        <li>You have tested and verified device behavior before going live</li>
                    </ul>

                    <h3>5.4 Third-Party Device Terms</h3>
                    <p>You must comply with the terms and conditions of all smart device manufacturers and platforms you integrate. We assume no responsibility for device compatibility, performance, or adherence to manufacturer specifications.</p>
                </section>

                <section class="policy-section">
                    <h2>6. Prohibited Activities</h2>
                    <p>You agree not to use TauchoPortal to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Violate any applicable laws, regulations, or third-party rights</li>
                        <li>Spam, harass, abuse, or threaten other users</li>
                        <li>Impersonate or misrepresent yourself or others</li>
                        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorized access to our systems or other users' accounts</li>
                        <li>Use automated scripts, bots, or tools to scrape or extract data (except as authorized by our API)</li>
                        <li>Transmit malware, viruses, or malicious code</li>
                        <li>Create or distribute phishing content or fraudulent schemes</li>
                        <li>Circumvent security measures or access restrictions</li>
                        <li>Interfere with the functionality or performance of the Service</li>
                        <li>Use the Service for illegal activities or to promote illegal content</li>
                        <li>Reverse engineer, decompile, or attempt to derive the source code of our Service</li>
                        <li>Manipulate stream data or automate fake engagement</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="policy-section">
                    <h2>7. User Content and Conduct</h2>
                    
                    <h3>7.1 Content Monitoring</h3>
                    <p>We automatically monitor stream chat messages and viewer interactions to identify trigger conditions. By using our Service, you acknowledge that your streaming content and audience interactions will be processed by our systems.</p>

                    <h3>7.2 User Responsibility</h3>
                    <p>You are solely responsible for the content you create and share through your streams. We do not monitor or control user-generated content, stream content, or viewer interactions. You must comply with all applicable laws and platform policies regarding your streaming content.</p>

                    <h3>7.3 Content Restrictions</h3>
                    <p>We reserve the right to suspend or terminate service for streams or conditions that involve:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Hate speech, discrimination, or targeted harassment</li>
                        <li>Sexual exploitation or child safety violations</li>
                        <li>Violence or dangerous activities</li>
                        <li>Copyright or intellectual property violations</li>
                        <li>Fraudulent or deceptive practices</li>
                    </ul>
                </section>

                <section class="policy-section">
                    <h2>8. Intellectual Property Rights</h2>
                    
                    <h3>8.1 Our Content</h3>
                    <p>All content on TauchoPortal, including but not limited to software, documentation, graphics, design, and logos, is owned by or licensed to TauchoPortal and protected by copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws. You may not reproduce, distribute, modify, or transmit this content without our express written permission.</p>

                    <h3>8.2 User Content License</h3>
                    <p>By using TauchoPortal, you grant us a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to use, reproduce, modify, and display any data or configurations you input into our Service, solely for the purpose of providing and improving the Service.</p>

                    <h3>8.3 Third-Party Content</h3>
                    <p>TauchoPortal may contain links to or integrate with third-party services. Intellectual property rights for those services are owned by their respective owners. We claim no rights to third-party content.</p>
                </section>

                <section class="policy-section">
                    <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
                    <p>TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, TAUCHOPORTAL AND ITS OFFICERS, DIRECTORS, EMPLOYEES, AND AGENTS SHALL NOT BE LIABLE FOR:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages</li>
                        <li>Loss of revenue, profits, data, or business opportunities</li>
                        <li>Damage to property or equipment</li>
                        <li>Service interruptions or system failures</li>
                        <li>Unauthorized access or data breaches (except to the extent caused by our gross negligence)</li>
                        <li>Actions taken by smart devices or unintended device behavior</li>
                        <li>Issues with third-party streaming platforms or services</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>This limitation applies even if TauchoPortal has been advised of the possibility of such damages.</p>
